We need to show that if $n > 1$ and for all decks $d: \text{Fin } n \to \mathbb{N}$ where all elements are positive, and if for all pairs $j, k$, there exists a nonempty $S$ such that the arithmetic mean of $d(j)$ and $d(k)$ equals the geometric mean of the elements in $S$, then all elements in the deck must be equal.

