$\frac{d(j) + d(k)}{2} = \prod_{i \in S} (d(i))^{1/n}$

But if $d(j) \neq d(k)$, then the arithmetic mean is strictly between $d(j)$ and $d(k)$ (by the strict convexity of the arithmetic mean). The geometric mean can only equal the arithmetic mean if all elements in $S$ are equal and equal to both $d(j)$ and $d(k)$, which is a contradiction since $d(j) \neq d(k)$.

